!! Core concepts

!!! Location registry

A ''location'' is a named, typed container for files. Each is a tiddler tagged `$:/tags/rimir/file-upload/location` with JSON body defining `name`, `uriPrefix`, `basePath`, and `writable`. Locations can be:

* ''Built-in'' &mdash; the default `/files/` location ships with file-upload
* ''Auto-discovered'' &mdash; scattered-binaries creates location tiddlers from its profiles at boot (optional integration)
* ''User-created'' &mdash; added via the settings UI

The ''uri-resolver'' library module (`$:/plugins/rimir/file-upload/uri-resolver`) maps any `_canonical_uri` to a filesystem path using the location registry. All routes use this resolver instead of hardcoded paths.

!!! Artifact registry

Derived data (thumbnails, extractions, summaries) is linked to parent file tiddlers via:

* `_artifact_source` &mdash; the parent tiddler's title
* `_artifact_type` &mdash; classification (`thumbnail`, `extraction`, `extraction-image`, `summary`)

When a file tiddler is deleted or renamed, all artifacts are automatically cascaded.

!! Data flow

!!! Upload

# Browser: user drops file onto `<$file-dropzone>` (with optional `location` attribute)
# Widget reads file via `wiki.readFiles()`, base64-encodes content
# Widget computes `targetPath` from MIME-type routing (or `subfolder` attribute)
# Widget performs XHR &rarr; `POST /api/file-upload` with `location` param
# Server resolves location via registry, validates MIME type, checks path traversal
# Server writes file to `<location.basePath>/<targetPath>`
# Server checks thumbnail settings &mdash; if enabled, runs ImageMagick via `runner-actions.json`
# Server responds with `{canonicalUri, filename, location, generatedUri?}`
# Widget executes `actions` callback with response variables

!!! Rename

# Browser: user saves tiddler with a new title
# `th-saving-tiddler` hook detects title change + `_canonical_uri` on original
# Hook looks up location via registry
# For writable locations: synchronous XHR &rarr; `POST /api/file-rename` (renames file + `_generated/`)
# For all locations: cascades rename to artifact tiddlers via `_artifact_source`
# Hook updates `_canonical_uri` on the new tiddler

!!! Delete

# Browser: user deletes a tiddler with `_canonical_uri`
# `th-deleting-tiddler` hook looks up location, shows confirmation dialog
# For writable locations: async XHR &rarr; `POST /api/file-delete` (deletes file + `_generated/` + `_derived/`)
# For all locations: cascades delete to artifact tiddlers via `_artifact_source`

!! Components

|!Component |!Layer |!Role |
|`uri-resolver.js` |Server |Shared library: URI-to-path resolution via location registry |
|`routes/upload.js` |Server |`POST /api/file-upload` &mdash; receive file, resolve location, write, run processor |
|`routes/rename.js` |Server |`POST /api/file-rename` &mdash; rename file at any writable location |
|`routes/delete.js` |Server |`POST /api/file-delete` &mdash; delete file at any writable location |
|`routes/serve-location.js` |Server |`GET /<prefix>/*` &mdash; serve files from user-created locations |
|`widgets/dropzone.js` |Browser |`<$file-dropzone>` with `location` attribute |
|`startup.js` |Browser |Lifecycle hooks with location-aware file ops + artifact cascade |
|`cascade-thumbnail.tid` |Browser |ViewTemplateBodyFilter for thumbnail rendering |
|`settings.tid` |Browser |Location management + thumbnail/upload settings |

!! Design decisions

* ''Location registry over hardcoded paths'' &mdash; all routes and hooks resolve URIs via the location registry. No path is hardcoded to `/files/`.
* ''Tag-based location tiddlers'' &mdash; standard TW pattern, queryable via filters. Scattered-binaries creates them at boot; users create them via UI.
* ''Artifact cascade via `_artifact_source` field'' &mdash; derived tiddlers back-reference their parent. Cascade logic queries `[_artifact_source[<title>]]` on delete/rename.
* ''Writable vs read-only'' &mdash; writable locations get full file ops; read-only locations get artifact cascade only (delete/rename the tiddler + artifacts, but not the physical file).
* ''`th-saving-tiddler` not `th-renaming-tiddler`'' &mdash; the editor's save-with-new-title flow uses `addTiddler` + `deleteTiddler`, not `wiki.renameTiddler()`.
* ''Synchronous XHR for rename'' &mdash; `th-saving-tiddler` must return the tiddler synchronously.
* ''`bodyFormat: "stream"` for upload'' &mdash; base64 files can be large; streaming avoids buffering limits.
* ''`_generated/` and `_derived/` subfolders'' &mdash; `_generated/` for thumbnails alongside the original; `_derived/` for multi-file extraction artifacts.
* ''Optional cross-plugin integration'' &mdash; scattered-binaries and llm-connect integrate via runtime feature detection. No hard dependencies.

!! Relink compatibility

file-upload ships a relink field config for `_artifact_source` (type: `title`). When the relink plugin is installed:

* ''Relink updates `_artifact_source`'' on artifact tiddlers when the referenced title changes
* ''Relink-titles'' may rename child tiddlers (e.g., `Report.pdf.extracted` &rarr; `NewName.pdf.extracted`) via its directory rule
* ''Our cascade runs first'' (`th-saving-tiddler` fires before `wiki.relinkTiddler()`) and handles file ops + artifact renames
* ''Belt-and-suspenders'' &mdash; both our cascade and relink update `_artifact_source`, but the cascade is defensive (skips already-renamed tiddlers, checks target existence)

Without relink: our cascade handles everything. With relink: both cooperate without conflict.

!! Security model

* MIME type whitelist &mdash; only types listed in `$:/config/rimir/file-upload/media-types` are accepted
* Path traversal &mdash; `resolveSecure()` verifies resolved paths stay inside the location's base directory
* Location writability &mdash; upload/delete/rename reject read-only locations
* CSRF &mdash; all POST routes require `X-Requested-With: TiddlyWiki` header
* File conflict &mdash; rename returns 409 if the target file already exists

